    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-24T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-24T09:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.01/12–2447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-24T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 24, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5536. Mytel 5398, December 16. Council of Ministers yesterday issued communiqué
                    announcing Bollaert given “full powers to undertake all action and negotiation
                    necessary for re-establishment of peace and liberty in Vietnam”. Communiqué
                    states that in view of failure of government of Ho Chi-minh to reply to offer of
                    negotiations made in Bollaert’s September 10 Haiphong [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Hadong</hi>] speech and Viet-minh radio’s rejection his offer, no
                    negotiations will be undertaken with government of Ho Chi-minh.</p>
                <p>Auriol, as President French Union, informed Council yesterday of receipt of
                    “active adherence” of Kingdoms of Cambodia and Laos to French Union.</p>
                <p>Department pass to Saigon as Paris 38.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
